# Framer Component Philosophy

Every component must:

- Render beautifully immediately with no configuration (default dimensions, content, colors)
- Expose designer-facing concepts, not engineering internals
- Be touch-safe and mobile-first — never assume hover exists
- Degrade gracefully under reduced motion, missing content, extreme aspect ratios, long text
- Survive portrait/landscape images, ultra-wide/narrow containers, mobile layouts
- Be self-contained — local state, props, minimal deps; no global state, no routing
- Be copy-paste portable, Storybook-compatible, and Framer-compatible
- Prevent invalid states via fallbacks, safe defaults, and constrained enums
- Use intentional animation that communicates state — avoid infinite loops or excessive springiness
- Expose curated config with opinionated defaults — not every parameter

**Bad controls:** `cubicBezier`, `perspectiveValue`, `transformOriginX`
**Good controls:** `Animation Style`, `Reveal Direction`, `Reveal On`, `Smoothness`
